***REMOVED***!/bin/sh
***REMOVED*** this is a simple xrandr script that adjusts the main display to 480p, intended for playing the visual novel Tsukihime, due to screen issues with that game

***REMOVED*** maindisplay=${"$(xrandr --listactivemonitors | grep -e '0:.*')"***REMOVED******REMOVED**** } ***REMOVED*** For some reason, this command only works with zsh. 
maindisplay=$(xrandr --listactivemonitors | grep -e '0:.*' | awk '{print $4}') ***REMOVED*** This is used to be more shell independent

xrandr --output "$maindisplay" --primary --mode ${1:-"640x480"}
